--- Updated Stop-server Command for servers ---
Adjusted the stop-server command to ensure it correctly identifies and terminates the server process, without forcing them.
This will involve implementing a more graceful shutdown procedure, allowing the server to close properly and avoid potential data loss or corruption.
It will send a command to the server console and send a windows close command if the console is not an input window.
We will user a powershell command to send a shutdown signal to the server process, allowing it to close gracefully.

--- Updated start-server Command for servers ---
Adjusted command to store the PID of the started server process in a more reliable way, ensuring that it can be 
accurately tracked and managed by the application.
Mainly by the "stop-server" command, which will now be able to reference the stored PID to terminate the correct process when needed.

